        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "## pKa Values for Citric Acid (Ligand: 2-Hydroxypropane-1,2,3-tricarboxylic acid)\n\nCitric acid is a **triprotic acid** (defined as H₃L in SRD-46). The three measured pKa values at **25 °C** and **I = 0.1 M** are:\n\n| Step | Equilibrium | pKa | T (°C) | I (mol/L) | VLM ID |\n|------|-------------|-----|---------|-----------|--------|\n| pKa₁ | H₂L ⇌ H₃L | **2.90** | 25 | 0.1 | vlm_157473 |\n| pKa₂ | HL ⇌ H₂L | **4.35** | 25 | 0.1 | vlm_157459 |\n| pKa₃ | L ⇌ HL | **5.65** | 25 | 0.1 | vlm_157439 |",
